{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Bvf1Ya1zVHorwYHBhuZY4Z","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ConfigMap `config-audit` is created in the `elasticsearch` namespace with 13,030 characters of findings. No cluster settings were modified.\n\nHere's a summary of what the audit found:\n\n**2 CRITICAL**\n- Security audit logging (`xpack.security.audit.enabled`) is absent from all node configs — authentication failures and data-access events are not recorded\n- No Kubernetes `NetworkPolicy` exists — any cluster pod can reach port 9200/9300\n\n**5 HIGH**\n- Transport SSL `verification_mode: certificate` (not `full`) — hostname/CN not validated between nodes\n- Built-in `elastic` superuser enabled with a static password in a Kubernetes Secret\n- File-realm `ops-user` is mapped to `superuser` — overly broad privileges\n- Master nodes also serve data/ingest/ML roles — no role separation for quorum protection\n- No snapshot repositories configured — no backup/recovery capability\n- Elasticsearch 8.11.1 is ~30 months behind the patch train\n\n**8 MEDIUM**\n- No TLS protocol or cipher restrictions configured explicitly\n- Multiple built-in system users (kibana, logstash, beats, apm) are enabled but their services are absent\n- `action.auto_create_index: true` — any client can create indices\n- `bootstrap.memory_lock: false` — heap may swap to disk\n- No ILM policy on either user index (`test-index`, `app-data`)\n- No index-level security (field/document-level filtering)\n- Pod `securityContext` missing `runAsNonRoot`, `allowPrivilegeEscalation: false`, capability drops\n- Kubernetes Secrets not encrypted at rest (etcd)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":329,"cache_read_input_tokens":60015,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":329},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"n